---
title: Migration: Resolve problems with PostgreSQL and Codeigniter
author: Federico Ponzi
username: federicoponzi
date: 2014-10-08
categories: [postgresql, codeigniter]
---

Resolve problem with #codeigniter and #postgres : After migrating to the new VM, you could have some problem.
These are some stesp to help you debug your problems:

1. Remember: the vm's URL has changed. Update $config['base_url'] variabile inside the application/config/config.php file.
2. Be sure that postgresql is installed: sudo apt-get install postgresql-9.3 
3. Be sure that your database exists, and check the credentials inside application/config/database.php
4. Be sure that php-postgre drivers are installed: `sudo apt-get install php5-pgsql` and then: `sudo service apache2 restart`
5. Inside application/config/database.php, set be sure that:`$db['default']['db_debug'] = FALSE;`
